Peter Dada An eight-year-old boy died  in  Owena town,  Idanre Local Government Area of Ondo State, after he was allegedly knocked down by a truck driver. The boy  identified as Kalid was  said to be hawking  pap when he was killed. It was learnt that the truck driver lost control of the vehicle following break failure and hit the hawker  who was coming from the opposite direction. A source told our correspondent that following the incident,  some youths in  the area attacked   the driver. The source said, “It was the quick  intervention of the police and soldiers  who rushed  to the scene that  saved the truck driver from being lynched.” The spokesman for the police in the state, Femi Joseph, confirmed the incident, saying  they had commenced  investigation into the matter. Copyright PUNCH.
